The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Wildlife
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      Wildlife
                            
	New Delhi, March 18: The environment and forests ministry may be split through the creation of a wildlife ministry, according to a source who attended a National Board of Wildlife (NBWL) meeting.         
	The non-official members of the NBWL had recommended the bifurcation of environment and wildlife tasks.         
	The 45-member NBWL is chaired by Prime Minister Manmohan Singh and has 15 non-official members. The non-official members recommended the new ministry  he agreed, the source said.         
	Environment and forests minister Jairam Ramesh was not available for comment.        
	We are hoping that this bifurcation will bring in more focus on wildlife issues, the source said.                                                                                                                                                          
